comments: Kanter (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Ball's (NOP) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Kanter (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Ball's (NOP) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Jones Jr. (POR) makes contact to Williamson's (NOP) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Covington (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Ball's (NOP) path and does not deliver contact.
Williamson (NOP) jumps along Lillard's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Covington's (POR) path and absorbs the contact.
Ball (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Covington's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Jones Jr. (POR) briefly places a stayed hand to Ingram's (NOP) front and removes it contesting his jump shot attempt.
Kanter (POR) and Hernangomez (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Redick (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Covington's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Covington (POR) moves laterally into Williamson's (NOP) path and the contact affects his SQBR.
Correctly called delay of game violation on NOP.
Ball (NOP) turns into and delivers contact to Lillard's (POR) body that affects his driving shot attempt.

Ingram (NOP) drives to the basket and Covington (POR) reaches in and makes contact with the ball at about the 00:10.0 mark, causing Ingram to briefly lose control.  Ingram regains possession of the ball in mid-air and is allowed to land before making the pass.
Anthony (POR) makes incidental contact to Ingram's (NOP) arm after the release of his driving shot attempt.
